****************************
Termius New November Edition
****************************

-------------------------------------------------------
=E2=9A=A1=EF=B8=8F Real-Time Collaboration, Now More Reliable Than Ever
-------------------------------------------------------

Multiplayer in Termius uses *WebRTC* to create a secure, end-to-end encrypt=
ed, peer-to-peer connection between teammates. However, until now, collabor=
ation sessions have often failed to connect when participants were behind s=
trict NAT or firewall configurations.

That's no longer the case.

We've added *several* *TURN* servers to handle those edge cases, ensuring y=
our Multiplayer sessions connect smoothly and stay stable, regardless of th=
e network setup.

Whether you're guiding a teammate through a tricky deployment or pair-debug=
ging a production issue, you can now rely on a more resilient connection ev=
ery time.

Read the full story behind the Multiplayer =E2=86=92 ( https://termius.com/=
blog/from-chaos-to-clarity-reimagining-real-time-collaboration-in-the-termi=
nal?utm_source=3Dnewsletter )

-----------------------------
=F0=9F=93=81 SFTP. Reimagined for Mobile
-----------------------------

We've completely reimagined SFTP in Termius to make file management on mobi=
le faster, smoother, and more flexible than ever.

The classic two-pane layout was great for one-off transfers. Unfortunately,=
 it made switching between servers and pushing files to multiple environmen=
ts difficult. The new SFTP changes that.

You can now:

* Open *multiple SFTP* connections in tabs.
* *Switch between Terminal and SFTP* with a single tap.
* Track file transfers in real-time and=C2=A0view *progress at a glance*.
* Access and upload files directly from your device's storage.

Whether you're updating configs, reviewing logs, or moving assets between s=
ervers, Termius now makes it easy from your phone.

The new SFTP experience, launched on iOS earlier this year, is now rolling =
out on Android.

Read the full story =E2=86=92 ( https://termius.com/blog/rethinking-sftp-fo=
r-mobile?utm_source=3Dnewsletter )

